Subject: Current Focal Point

Description: Compact attention-direction packet to reload after context compression.

& [CurrentFocalPoint] is the live re-entry seed for active focus
  + [status] is active
  + [renewal_reason] is preserve focused attention across context compression
  + [focus_subject] is periphery correlation corpus worker candidate
  + [focus_mode] is mixed_focus
  + [executive_drive] is keep the OS clock running by committing, reporting, reviewing, emitting a loop tick, and stepping into the next safe runnable frame
  + [right_hemisphere_draw] is evidence_review passed on the first attempt and the next movement should test whether the worker can brainstorm correlations without treating them as proof
  + [inside] is 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_011.sop, lmstudio_diverse_corpus_launch_queue_002.sop, evidence_review_review_013.sop, periphery_correlation_prompt_014.sop, LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop, LMStudioAgentBenchmark.sop, and AttentionRuntimeRegistryState.sop
  + [boundary] is continue only when clock_state is running and the candidate remains inspectable, scratch-isolated, exact-output, content-filled, literal-term complete, ASCII-stable, captured, and validator-gated; pause or block on user stop, credentials, destructive action, missing authority, project-root LM Studio authority, broad competence claims, automatic launch, or unrelated dirty files
